{"tid":758257,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"碧咸講普通話拍澳門威尼斯人廣告 引爆網民狂插","createTime":"2018-07-27T13:41:41.000Z","updateTime":"2018-07-27T15:27:03.000Z","uid":14918,"like":3,"dislike":7,"uniUserReply":17,"replies":[{"pid":"9b2e67862b2d2e089bd2ad3d16e7f6d99a7580be","tid":758257,"uid":14918,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-07-27T13:41:41.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"http://photos.prnasia.com/prnk/20180718/2190108-1\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=http%3A%2F%2Fphotos.prnasia.com%2Fprnk%2F20180718%2F2190108-1&h=015070fa&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">The advert set in Macau, features Beckham and film stars from China and Hong Kong including Qiao Shan, Lam Suet and Helena Law, on a quest to find the perfect egg tart &ndash; a delicacy of Portuguese origin for which Macau, a former Portuguese territory, is famous.</span><br />\n<br />\nCantonese is the mother tongue of Hong Kong, no matter how much Mandarin you hear<br />\n<br />\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Internet users who left comments on Beckham&rsquo;s official Facebook page were not impressed with his language choice.<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://cdn2.i-scmp.com/sites/default/files/images/methode/2018/07/27/ec57b2b2-9081-11e8-ad1d-4615aa6bc452_1320x770_181802.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn2.i-scmp.com%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fimages%2Fmethode%2F2018%2F07%2F27%2Fec57b2b2-9081-11e8-ad1d-4615aa6bc452_1320x770_181802.jpg&h=3e7e444e&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;Our mother language is Cantonese and we write and read traditional Chinese. I know that you should not be involved in the complicated political issues and culture conflicts in Hong Kong and Macau, but this advertisement shows nothing about Macau at all,&rdquo; wrote one user.<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://cdn1.i-scmp.com/sites/default/files/images/methode/2018/07/27/f0a45c86-9094-11e8-ad1d-4615aa6bc452_972x_181802.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn1.i-scmp.com%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fimages%2Fmethode%2F2018%2F07%2F27%2Ff0a45c86-9094-11e8-ad1d-4615aa6bc452_972x_181802.jpg&h=00838767&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\nMandarin is written using simplified Chinese characters, whereas Cantonese speakers in Hong Kong and Macau use traditional Chinese characters. </span><br />\n<br />\nYou could never replace Cantonese as the language of Hong Kong <br />\n<br />\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">In similar vein were comments such as: &ldquo;Hello David, why don&rsquo;t you speak Cantonese? Because Macau and Hong Kong people all speak Cantonese,&rdquo; and, &ldquo;I would rather you speak English instead of Mandarin in the video.&rdquo;</span><br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">One commenter had a few things to say: &ldquo;Dear superstar sir &ndash; the money-friendly David Beckham, regarding the Venetian commercial, here are few things I want you to know.<br />\n<br />\n1. We (Macanese) speak Cantonese or Portuguese only!<br />\n<br />\n2. Portuguese egg tart &amp; traditional egg tart are two different things!<br />\n<br />\nPlease respect our culture while you&rsquo;re making friends and money from mainland [Chinese]! SINCERELY YOURS.&rdquo;</span>"},{"pid":"062d262331acc9bd8f5c048ef18472fb2b75a02a","tid":758257,"uid":155818,"like":0,"dislike":21,"score":-21,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-07-27T13:43:03.000Z","msg":"澳門係講澳門架啦<br />\n有搞錯咩?"},{"pid":"7647a4e733b5b747bf651b1c1392e1ee467d4b9d","tid":758257,"uid":155818,"like":9,"dislike":1,"score":8,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-07-27T13:43:35.000Z","msg":"<blockquote>澳門係講<strong><span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\"><span style=\"color: red;\">普通話</span></span></strong>架啦<br />\n有搞錯咩?</blockquote>"},{"pid":"24ffc1930425477f501d6e8e72f287ef53330061","tid":758257,"uid":57410,"like":2,"dislike":3,"score":-1,"quote":{"pid":"7647a4e733b5b747bf651b1c1392e1ee467d4b9d","tid":758257,"uid":155818,"lik